Hammer 73pt bonus @60<br>
<br>
When the hammer lands it will have a 41pt advantage in the damage bonus category every hit.<br>
<br>
Math and physics can prove that an elephant can hang from the side of a cliff with it's tail tied to a daisy. Please keep that in mind when you so vehemetly make statements about haste/ratios/etc.<br>
<br>
I'd MUCH rather swing a 74/44 weapon with a damage bonus of 73pts that also gives me 160hp 15str and about 8ac (which consequently for me, negates the wt on it) over a 38/18 with a 32pt damage bonus.<br>
<br>
Personally I'd never use a 2hb if I was main tanking in a group as 2hb just don't build the same agro, unless they proc (and alot) as dual wielding.<br>
<br>
2hb in my opinion is raid only, and ass end of mob in xping groups.<br>
<br>
160hp helps in an AOE/mass flurry encounter.<br>
<br>
My bard has one level to go for battlecry - 15% over the 100 cap, and 9 levels for Warcry - 25% over the 100 cap.<br>
<br>
But I'm sure I'm not going to convince anyone without logs, so I'll continue to auction for one in game and on my server boards, and camp the spot where it drops and post the logs so you can see why I believe the hammer is better :)<br>
<br>
Also keep in mind that no matter what 2hb you use, you have the SAME chance to miss with it as any other 2hb, unless that 2hb has a modifier on it +10% to miss. So while the IFS is getting more chances to land, it has to to keep up with the damage output of the Dathor which I'm convinced it won't.<br>
<br>
This is another reason I was looking for Crit calculations earlier, your crits are going to be MUCH larger on the dathor as well and I have CF1. Again you have the same chance to crit on the IFS as the Dathor unless one has a modifier +10% to not crit. <p><center><img src="http://home.kc.rr.com/ssvanti/sig2.gif" border="0" width="467" height="152"><br>
