<br>
a) Hammer and IFS will repost the same but hammer will do significantly more damage then IFS when this happens.<br>
<br>
b) You will get fewer reposts while hammering then swinging the IFS so you take less damage.<br>
<br>
c) The damage bonus on the hammer is significantly larger then on the IFS.<br>
<br>
The big draw back on the hammer for everyday use is simply the weight.<br>
<br>
But consider FD soloing.   It would be just great to have this hammer for FD soloing whith aa points in rapid feign.  And some nice hast then the delay of the hammer should match up rather well with the repop of FD.<br>
<br>
I would love to have the hammer and will leave the simplistic comparisons of damage / delay ratios to the simpletons.  The hammer in the tink bag would be a great card to play from time to time.<br>
